cli-parm.name: allowmultiplesuppliers
cli-parm.tip: Allow any construct to have multiple suppliers

cli-parm.name: application
cli-parm.tip: Name of the application, i.e. root package in UML

cli-parm.name: arguments
cli-parm.tip: Path to the file holding (additional) arguments (in the form key = value)

cli-parm.name: debug
cli-parm.tip: Yes if run in debug mode

cli-parm.name: debugmode
cli-parm.tip: If debug=yes, then the debug mode must be any of the codes specified between ";". The main chain is "CHAIN".

cli-parm.name: docrelease
cli-parm.tip: If supplied, this is a documentation release with specified release date

cli-parm.name: forcecompile
cli-parm.tip: Force a compile and ignore possible errors

cli-parm.name: help
cli-parm.tip: Print program help and copyright/license info for this application

cli-parm.name: jobid
cli-parm.tip: An ID for this particular run of Imvertor

cli-parm.name: language
cli-parm.tip: Language of the metamodel and model. Specify metamodel:model, like "en:nl", or single code for both.

cli-parm.name: messagecollapsekeys
cli-parm.tip: If similar messages should be collapsed, provide a space-separated list of keys for these types of messages.

cli-parm.name: messagelevel
cli-parm.tip: Set the message level to error (no warnings) or warning (errors and warnings)

cli-parm.name: nativescalars
cli-parm.tip: Yes if scalar types may be entered without reference to a UML datatype

cli-parm.name: normalizeids
cli-parm.tip: Yes if XMI based ID's should be normalized, i.e. reduced to unique strings valid for Imvertor processing

cli-parm.name: processingmode
cli-parm.tip: Specify the processing mode. This takes the form "Owner:Meta:Stage"

cli-parm.name: profilemode
cli-parm.tip: Specify for which stylesheets (identified by code) a runtime profile must be generated. Codes are specified between ";". Profiling is only available when debug=yes.

cli-parm.name: project
cli-parm.tip: Name of the project

cli-parm.name: proxyurl
cli-parm.tip: Reliable URL for testing internet connection

cli-parm.name: signaldeadurls
cli-parm.tip: Yes if a warning should, be issued for each inaccessible URL detected in notes and tagged values.

cli-parm.name: suppresswarnings
cli-parm.tip: Yes if warnings should be suppressed in documentation

cli-parm.name: task
cli-parm.tip: Set task to compile or release

cli-parm.name: umlfile
cli-parm.tip: Path to the input UML file, must be EAP or XMI

cli-parm.name: userid
cli-parm.tip: ID of the user who started this run

cli-parm.name: versionrules
cli-parm.tip: Name of the version rules file

cli-parm.name: visuals
cli-parm.tip: Name of the visuals file. If omitted, assume metamodel name and version as extracted from the supplied model.

cli-parm.name: xlinkversion
cli-parm.tip: Version of the xlinks specification
